  <h1>Slightly Sweet Soured‑Milk Waffles</h1>

  <h2>Ingredients (4 round waffles)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>1 ¾ cups (225 g) all‑purpose flour <span class="note">optional: replace ¼ cup with cornstarch for extra crispness</span></li>
    <li>2 Tbsp (25 g) granulated sugar</li>
    <li>1 ½ tsp (6 g) baking powder</li>
    <li>¼ tsp (1 g) baking soda</li>
    <li>½ tsp fine sea salt</li>
    <li>1 ¾ cups (415 mL) whole or 2 % milk
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Souring step:</strong> Stir in 1 Tbsp (15 mL) fresh lemon juice <em>or</em> white vinegar, then let stand 5 minutes until slightly thickened.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>2 large eggs, separated</li>
    <li>4 Tbsp (60 g) unsalted butter, melted &amp; cooled</li>
    <li>1 tsp (5 mL) pure vanilla extract</li>
    <li>Optional mix‑ins: a handful of mini chocolate chips, blueberries, or toasted pecans (&lt; ½ cup total)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Equipment</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Cuisinart 2‑in‑1 Waffle &amp; Pancake Maker</li>
    <li>Two mixing bowls + whisk</li>
    <li>Hand mixer (or vigorous whisk) for egg whites</li>
    <li>Measuring cups &amp; spoons, ladle (~⅔ cup capacity)</li>
    <li>Wire rack for finished waffles</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Method</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Preheat:</strong> Set the Cuisinart to <em>WAFFLE → Medium‑High (about 4 of 5)</em>. Close the lid and allow at least 5 minutes to heat. Lightly oil the plates.</li>
    <li><strong>Combine dry:</strong> In a large bowl whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.</li>
    <li><strong>Mix wet:</strong> In a second bowl whisk together egg yolks, melted butter, vanilla, and the <em>soured milk</em>.</li>
    <li><strong>Batter:</strong> Pour wet mixture into dry. Stir just until you no longer see dry flour (some lumps are fine).</li>
    <li><strong>Whip whites:</strong> Beat egg whites to soft peaks; fold gently into batter in two additions.</li>
    <li><strong>Cook:</strong> Ladle ~⅔ cup batter onto center of waffle plate, close lid, and cook 3 ½–4 min until steam subsides and waffle is golden. Add 30 s if needed for deeper color.</li>
    <li><strong>Hold/crisp:</strong> Transfer waffles to a wire rack or 95 °C (200 °F) oven for up to 20 min while you finish the batch.</li>
    <li><strong>Serve:</strong> Sprinkle with powdered sugar and top with warm maple syrup mixed with a spoonful of crème fraîche. Fresh berries optional.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Make‑Ahead Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Freeze cooled waffles in a single layer, then bag. Reheat from frozen in a toaster on medium.</li>
    <li>Batter keeps 24 h in the fridge (it will deflate slightly).</li>
  </ul>
